{"/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_calhoun_ver01/data/sn83016244/00513689937/1958050401/0039.xml":{"full_text":"Mini-Golf Is\nNew Southard\nSt Fun Came\nSouthard Street\u2019s amusement\narea added another extra- color\nful attraction this weak with the\nopening of the intriguing \u201cMini-\nGolf Course\u201d next to the Skating\nRirf.\nMorton Thomas, who runs the\nskating rink and other amuse\nment Concessions in the block\nbetween Duval and Whitehead, is\nmanager of the new recreation fa\ncility.\nThe colorful little outdoor golf\ncourse at 420 Southard St. fea\ntures well known landmarks\nfrom points around the world as\nits hole markers. Miniatures of\nParis\u2019 Eiffel Tower, London\u2019s Big\nBen, Holland\u2019s windmills, and Ita.\nly\u2019s Leaning Tower of Pisa are\namong the landscaping features.\nThe course is lighted for night\nplay.\nThomas points out that the\ngame is fun for youngsters wait\ning for parents to finish shopping,\nfor aduKa wishing to while away\nan hour or two or for couples,\nout \u201con the town,\" as an addition\nto an evening of amusement.\nWilliam Henry Harrison, a Whig,\nserved as President of the United\nStates for only one month before\nhe died in IMI.\nHappy To Serve\nYour\nBuilding\nRequirements\nSTRUNK\nLUMBER YARD\nIN SIMONTON STRUT\nPHONI CY 4-9091\nJUST IN TIME\nzAIA. For Mother\u2019s Day!\nORCHID SALE\nBOTANICALS\nCATLEYAS\nVANDAS\nOsmunds Fir Bark Fern Slabs\nBaskets and Pots\nCORSAGE MATERIALS\nFor Do-It-Yourgelferi!\nKey West Garden\nand PET SUPPLY\nIM FUMING STREET PHONE CY 6-6912\nI I\nI*W\nI k*TL JI E\ngrocery shopping right at home... J\nwith an ELECTRIC FREEZER!\nh's the wonderful convenience, more than anything else, that makes an\nelectric food freezer a \"must\u201d for every home.\nSure, you save money, too\u2014by buying in quantity and at seasonal\nlow prices. You save money by shopping loss often, by freezing left-overs,\nby processing your own frosh vegetables.\nlut the real payoff is the day-to-day convenience of having a whole R\n\"grocery store\" right in your home of guide, oasy meal preparation\nof \"stockpiles\" of food when guests drop in unexpectedly... of R\nadvance preparation for parties, school lunches, special occasions. g\nBuy an electric freezer for your h0m0... for bettor living, electrically!\nCITY ELECTRIC J\nSYSTEM O\nPROPOSED NEW LIBRARY\u2014This is what Menroa County's now public library in Key West will look like If built to plans drawn by\narchitect William H. Merriam. Merriam submitted plans and the above sketch to the Monroe County Library Association at a mooting\nWednesday at the Key West Woman's Club. The library association's board of directors and planning board, with $40,000 in hand, need\nonly $lO,OOO mere to build the new facility. (Sao story, Page 1.)\nSouthern Bell V.P. Outlines\nGood State Business Outlook\nC. J. Yates, vice president and\ngeneral manager of Southern Bell\nTelephone Company and president\nof the Florida State Chamber of\nCommerce, was elected to mem\nbership of the Alpha of Florida\nChapter of the Beta Gamma Sig\nma, the national honorary busi\nness fraternity.\nThe selection of Yates as the\nFlorida business man to receive\nthe honorary membershp was bas\ned on \u201caccomplishments in the\npublic utility and Chamber of\nCommerce fields\u201d and for \u201cdem\nonstrated interest in collegiate\ntraining for business.\u201d\nIn addressing the Alpha Chap\nter\u2019s annual banquet, Yates said,\n\u201cThis honor should rightfully go\nto the men and women of the\ncompany and the Florida State\nChamber of Commerce whose ef\nforts and accomplishments have\nmade this honor possible.\u201d\nAs principal speaker at the ban\nquet, Yates paid tribute to the\nfraternity membership and to the\nUniversity of Florida. He pointed\nout that \u2018You will have the best\npossible foundation for a success\nful business career but, a bus\ninessman\u2019s education is never\ncompleted. Business changes from\nyear to year and business men\nmust change with conditions if\nthey are to continue to be success\nful.\"\nYate* said, \u201cIn Florida we are\nfortunate in having one of the\nbest business climates in the coun\ntry.\" He attributed this to state\nand local tax structures, regula\ntions and restrictions applicable\nto business operations and charac\nter and integrity of our public\nofficials.\nIn commenting on opportuni\nties for young businnessmen in\nFlorida, Yates said, \u201cI know of\nno other state which offers better\nopportunity.\u201d\n\u201cDuring the last six years, bus\niness concerns in Florida increas\ned 26.9 per cent yet nationwide\nTurner-Farmer Of fere Service\nAir-Conditioners\nHome-Demonstrated\nExtra service is the watchword\nof Bob Turner and George Farm\ner, who In January, 1958, formed\nthe Turner Farmer Air Condi\ntioning Co. here and were award\ned a Fedders franchise.\nTurner, local manager of Lowry\nElectric Co. and George Farmer,\nwho has been in the auto business\nhere for some seven years, have\na mobile display truck to dem\nonstrate Fedders air conditioner!\nto prospective buyers at their\nhomes.\nA request from a prospective\nbusiness concerns decreased 22\nper cent. In 1957, a record of 853\nnew Florida industrial plants and\nexpansions created more than 25,-\n000 new jobs.\u201d\n\u201cIn business (Southern Bell),\"\nYates said, \u201c1742 or 14.8 per cent\nof the people on the payroll\nas of January 1, 1957 were ad\nvanced or promoted to higher\npaying jobs.\u201d In concluding his\ntalk, Yates said the greatest need\nin any business is for people who\nhave the \u2018know how\u201d and the\n\u201cdesire\u201d to get the job done.\nTHIS PRICE\nINCLUDES\nDELIVERY\nTO YOUR\nDOOR!\nThis Unit Has\nAll the\nFine\nFeatures\nFound In\nFedders\u2019\nSummer Air-\nConditioners!\nAsk Anyone\nWho Owns A\nFEDDERS and\nTHEY WILL\nTELL YOU WHY\nFEDDERS is the\nLARGEST\nSELLING\nAIR\nCONDITIONER\nIN THE\nWORLD!\ncustomer will bring the truck to\nhis home any afternoon or even\ning.\nSince the possible \u201cextra costs\"\nof air conditioning, such as in\nstallation fees, rewiring homes to\ncarry the added load and service\ncosts on the air conditioner after\nit's brought have sometimes been\na problem, the Turner-Farmer\npersonnel gave extra service here.\nAfter demonstrating the unit of\nthe buyer's choice in the mobile\ndisplay, they will give him a\ncomplete estimate on the cost of\ninstalling it, check his wiring,\ngive him an estimate on the cost\nof putting In heavier wiring if it\u2019s\nneeded (which is seldom neces\nsary for one horsepower or\nsmaller air conditioners) and give\nhim the details of service on the\nunit if it's ever needed.\nIn short, the Turner Farmer\npersonnel will furnish the custom\ner with a complete figure on how\nmuch the air conditioner will cost,\ninstalled and operating.\nThere is no charge or obliga\ntion for the demonstrations and\ncost estimates, Turner and Farmer\nsaid.\nFEDDERS\nWorld\"s Largest Sailing...\na^MAd air conditioners\n115 VOlt\n^^RT^^included\nSTYLE\nSMAfT LOOKIN'- FAST COOLIN\u2019-\nl/C SOOM Alt CONDITION\" AT\nA SENSATIONAL SAVING!\nI I\nKf PERFORMANCE\n1 SHtD K\u00bb QUIfT O'tIATION\nCOOLS-VINTILATfS-tXHAUSTS-\nOtHUMIDIFItS AND TILTHS!\nW CONVENIENCE HI\nMOST COMPACT WALL CAtINtT...\nWITH SUDFOUV OllfD-FOt-LIFt\natniGttANT systimi NEW 1951\nOMI di\neconomy ^KRNr (mown awvi) Igs\u00dffSuA\nPIVf FACTORY WAttANTY Af f WUK\nffagfiKiNG ALL\n^ALBS'RECOF^:\nTURNER-FARMER\nAIR-CONDITIONING COMPANY\nCOMPLETE FACTORY-AUTHORIZED SERVICE\nShowroom: 829 CAROLINE STREET \u2014CY 641233\nWarehouse: At Lowry Electric Company, Stock Island, CY 6-8630\nCity Permits\nOnly $4,980\nIn Past Week\nOnly repairs and a few addi\ntions were apparently started by\nKey Westers this week as City\nBuilding Official Ray Knopp\u2019s of\nfice issued permits for $4,980\nworth of construction.\nThe complete list of permits Is\nas follows;\nJ. R. Roberts, 923 Angela Street,\nminor repairs, $300., owner.\nF. Sands, 413 Smith Lane, minor\nrepairs, $2OO owner.\nj. H. Richardson. 14(M Newton\nStreet, addition. $500., owner.\nV. Conly, Duck and 15th Sts.,\naddition, $BO., owner.\nD. Garrido, 1012 Watson Street,\nminor repairs, $300., owner.\nR. Garcia, Sr., MM Patricia\nStreet, General Repairs, $500.,\nowner.\nW. B. Lanier, 912 James Street,\naddition, $2,100., O. G. Koehn.\nW. A. Washington 1403 Olivia\nStreet, addition, $125.\nC. H. Harrow, 1701 Petronia\nStreet, fence, $150., owner.\nF. L. Johnson, 1415 Newton\nStreet, carport repairs, $130., own\ner.\nR. R. Valdes, 1211 Laird Street,\naddition, $490., owner.\nE. Sumner, 308 Catherine Street,\nrepair porch, $85., owner.\nAustralia today has more sheep\nand cattle than ever before. Sta\ntistics reported st the end of 1957\nsaid there were 149,802.000 sheep\nand 17,257,000 cattle. There also\nwere 1,325,000 pigs and 737,000\nhorses.\nYlu-^Cge\nCONSTRUCTION CO.\n^o^B\nRESIDENTIAL\nCOMMERCIAL\nLAWRENCE PADRON\nGENERAL CONTRACTOR\nFINANCING ARRANGED\nVA\nFHA\nConventional Loans\n\"Bring Ua Your Plana\"\nCYpress 4-1451\n2311 FOGARTY AVI.\nBuMay, May 4,1981 TW MY WRIT CITIZBN\nApril Catch. Tops In 3 Years\nWeek\u2019s Shrimp Haul\nIs 419,000 Pounds\nBoats fishing out of Key West\nbrought more shrimp into port\nthis April than during any April\nfor the past three years, U. S. Fish\nand Wildlife Agent C. E. Nicker\nson said today.\nThe figures showed boats\nbrought 1,767,875 pounds of shrimp\n1,745.258 from the Tortugas\nbeds and 22,617 from Campeche\nto local docks last month. The\nApril 1957 total figure was 787,-\n826 from both fishing areas and\nth- April 1956 total, 1.205.532.\n\u201cThe reports also show an in\ncrease in production over March\nthis year,\u201d Nickerson said. \"In\nMarch, 1,726,871 pounds of shrimp\nwere landed here.\u201d\nLast week, boats brought in a\nwhopping 419,000 pounds of the\npink seafood, 408,900 pounds from\nthe nearby Tortugas area and 10.-\n100 pounds from the Campeche\nbeds across the Gulf of Mexico.\nThis was six times the 70,700\npounds of shrimp landed during\nthe week ending April 25, 1957,\nwhen a steady East wind kept\nmost boats In port. Only 43,200\npounds of shrimp from Tortugas\nB AWNING\nWINDOW\nBy\nCROSSLY\nAbo\nCROSSLY\nJALOUSIE\nWindows and\nDoors\nT\u00abd\u00ab0 Meat Dependable, RtMomlMl, and Proetkol\nAluminum Winclaw.\nDistributed By:\nMONROE COUNTY\nGLASS MIRROR\n111 FUMING ST. CY MU\nand 27,500 from Campbeche were\nbrought in during that week.\nAlli the weights listed in Nick\nerson's report are the weight of\nshrimp after the heads have been\nremoved.\nShrimp Marking\nThe U. I. Fish and Wildlife\nService and University of Mia\nmi marine laberatery are\nmarking shrimp with red, blue\nand green dyes te study their'\ngrowth, movement and death\nrates.\nC. I. Nickerson, fish and\nwildlHo agent, said the dyes\ndon\u2019t affect tha shrimp's eat\ning quality and show up in\nthe head section, removed\nbefore eating anyhow.\nAnyone catching any of the\ncolored shrimp is asked to\nsave them, note the date and\nplace they were caught and\nnotify the University's mar\nine lab, 1 Rickenbacker Cause\nway, Virginia Key, Miami, 49,\nFlorida, or the fish and wild\nlife service In Miami, High\nland 4-1703.\nTHIS PRICE\nINCLUDES\nPARTS and\nSERVICE for\nONE YEAR!\nSimply\nPlug\nIt\nInto Your\nPresent\nElectrical\nOutlet\nCALL US-\nWe Will Bring\nOur\nMobile Display\nTo Your Home\nand\nDemonstrate\nThis\nAmazing Unit\nWITHOUT\nCHARGE or\nOBLIGATION!\nPage 15","height":"28959","width":"19858"}}
